Assignment Questions Statistics Basic-2 Assignment Data Science Masters
 Q1. What are the three measures of central tendency? 
Mean median and mode are the three measures of central tendencies
Q2. What is the difference between the mean, median, and mode? How are they used to measure the central tendency of a dataset? 
The mean is the arithmetic average of all the data points in a dataset. It is calculated by summing up all the values and dividing by the total number of data points.
The median is the middle value of a dataset when the values are arranged in ascending or descending order.
The mode is the value that occurs most frequently in a dataset.
Q3. Measure the three measures of central tendency for the given height data:  [178,177,176,177,178.2,178,175,179,180,175,178.9,176.2,177,172.5,178,176.5] 
Mean ≈ 177.27
•	Median = 177.5
•	Mode = 178


Q4. Find the standard deviation for the given data: [178,177,176,177,178.2,178,175,179,180,175,178.9,176.2,177,172.5,178,176.5]
1.7845.
 Q5. How are measures of dispersion such as range, variance, and standard deviation used to describe the spread of a dataset? Provide an example. 
Range: The range is the simplest measure of dispersion and is calculated as the difference between the maximum and minimum values in the dataset. Range = Maximum value - Minimum value
Variance: The variance measures how far each data point is from the mean of the dataset.
Standard Deviation: The standard deviation is the square root of the variance and provides a measure of dispersion in the original unit of the data
Q6. What is a Venn diagram? 
A Venn diagram is a visual representation used to depict the relationships and similarities between different sets or groups of data.
Q7. For the two given sets A = (2,3,4,5,6,7) & B = (0,2,6,8,10). Find: (i) A B (ii) A ⋃ B 
A ∩ B = {2, 6}
A ⋃ B = {0, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 10}

Q8. What do you understand about skewness in data? 
Skewness in data refers to the measure of asymmetry or lack of symmetry in the distribution of data points in a dataset. In a symmetrical distribution, the data points are evenly distributed on both sides of the central point (mean, median, or mode), resulting in a balanced distribution
Q9. If a data is right skewed then what will be the position of median with respect to mean? 
If a data set is right-skewed, the position of the median will be to the left of the mean.

