 Q11. What is the formula for calculating the sample mean? Provide an example calculation for a dataset. 
Sample Mean (x̄) = (Sum of all data points) / (Total number of data points)
Dataset: [10, 15, 20, 25, 30]
Sum = 10 + 15 + 20 + 25 + 30 = 100
N=5
Sample Mean (x̄) = Sum / n 
Sample Mean (x̄) = 100 / 5 
Sample Mean (x̄) = 20

Q12. For a normal distribution data what is the relationship between its measure of central tendency? 
In a normal distribution, the relationship between its measures of central tendency (mean, median, and mode) is that they are all equal. In other words, the mean, median, and mode of a normal distribution have the same value
